an JM, Bettencourt LMA, Castillo-Chavez C, editors. <span class="ref-journal">Mathematical and Statistical Estimation Approaches in Epidemiology.</span> Springer; Dordrecht, Germany: 2009. pp. 103\xe2\x80\x93121. <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Mathematical+and+Statistical+Estimation+Approaches+in+Epidemiology&amp;author=H+Nishiura&amp;author=G+Chowell&amp;publication_year=2009&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2819789&amp;issue-id=185317&amp;journal-id=876&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="b19-ijerph-07-00291">19. <span class="element-citation">Shiboski SC, Jewell NP. Statistical analysis of the time dependence of HIV infectivity based on partner study data. <span><span class="ref-journal">J. Amer. Statist. Assn. </span>1991;<span class="ref-vol">87</span>:360\xe2\x80\x93372.</span> <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=J.+Amer.+Statist.+Assn&amp;title=Statistical+analysis+of+the+time+dependence+of+HIV+infectivity+based+on+partner+study+data&amp;author=SC+Shiboski&amp;author=NP+Jewell&amp;volume=87&amp;publication_year=1991&amp;pages=360-372&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2819789&amp;issue-id=185317&amp;journal-id=876&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="b20-ijerph-07-00291">20. <span class="element-citation">Hollingsworth TD, Anderson RM, Fraser C. HIV-1 transmission, by stage of infection. <span><span class="ref-journal">Int. J. Infect. Dis. </span>2008;<span class="ref-vol">198</span>:687\xe2\x80\x93693.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/18662132" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2819789&amp;issue-id=185317&amp;journal-id=876&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=